ic of twelve key figures from Conservative Party politics. Each chapter is written by an expert in the field and explores how its subject attempted to use oratory to advance their agenda within the party and beyond. This is the first book to analyse Conservative Party politics in this way, and marks an important new departure in the analysis of British politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPoliticiansxAttitudesxGreat Britain. 0aPoliticianszGreat BritainxAttitudes. 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Conservatism & Liberalism.2bisacsh  aConservative Party.  aconservatism.  aelectoral strategy.  aideological repositioning.  aoratory.  aparty strategy.  apolitical communication.  apolitical leadership.  arhetoric.1 aAtkins, Judi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBale, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBennister, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrines, Andrew S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDommett, Katharine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDorey, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Brendan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarnett, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarnett, Norton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHayton, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHayton, Richard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeppell, Timothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcMeeking, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.lo